00077 void* NSGLGetProcAddress (const GLubyte *name)
00078 {
00079   static void* image = NULL;
00080   if (NULL == image) 
00081   {
00082     image = dlopen("/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/Versions/Current/OpenGL", RTLD_LAZY);
00083   }
00084   return image ? dlsym(image, (const char*)name) : NULL;
00085 }
00086 #else
00087 
00088 #include <mach-o/dyld.h>
00089 
00090 void* NSGLGetProcAddress (const GLubyte *name)
00091 {
00092   static const struct mach_header* image = NULL;
00093   NSSymbol symbol;
00094   char* symbolName;
00095   if (NULL == image)
00096   {
00097     image = NSAddImage("/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/Versions/Current/OpenGL", NSADDIMAGE_OPTION_RETURN_ON_ERROR);
00098   }
00099   /* prepend a '_' for the Unix C symbol mangling convention */
00100   symbolName = malloc(strlen((const char*)name) + 2);
00101   strcpy(symbolName+1, (const char*)name);
00102   symbolName[0] = '_';
00103   symbol = NULL;
00104   /* if (NSIsSymbolNameDefined(symbolName))
00105          symbol = NSLookupAndBindSymbol(symbolName); */
00106   symbol = image ? NSLookupSymbolInImage(image, symbolName, NSLOOKUPSYMBOLINIMAGE_OPTION_BIND | NSLOOKUPSYMBOLINIMAGE_OPTION_RETURN_ON_ERROR) : NULL;
00107   free(symbolName);
00108   return symbol ? NSAddressOfSymbol(symbol) : NULL;
00109 }
00110 #endif /* MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_3 */
00111 #endif /* __APPLE__ */

00113 #if defined(__sgi) || defined (__sun)
00114 #include <dlfcn.h>
00115 #include <stdio.h>
00116 #include <stdlib.h>
00117 
00118 void* dlGetProcAddress (const GLubyte* name)
00119 {
00120   static void* h = NULL;
00121   static void* gpa;
00122 
00123   if (h == NULL)
00124   {
00125     if ((h = dlopen(NULL, RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_LOCAL)) == NULL) return NULL;
00126     gpa = dlsym(h, "glXGetProcAddress");
00127   }
00128 
00129   if (gpa != NULL)
00130     return ((void*(*)(const GLubyte*))gpa)(name);
00131   else
00132     return dlsym(h, (const char*)name);
00133 }
00134 #endif /* __sgi || __sun */

00142 #  if defined(__APPLE__)
00143 #    define glewGetProcAddress(name) NSGLGetProcAddress(name)
00144 #  else
00145 #    if defined(__sgi) || defined(__sun)
00146 #      define glewGetProcAddress(name) dlGetProcAddress(name)
00147 #    else /* __linux */
00148 #      define glewGetProcAddress(name) (*glXGetProcAddressARB)(name)
00149 #    endif
00150 #  endif
00151 #endif

00158 /*
00159  * GLEW, just like OpenGL or GLU, does not rely on the standard C library.
00160  * These functions implement the functionality required in this file.
00161  */
00162 static GLuint _glewStrLen (const GLubyte* s)
00163 {
00164   GLuint i=0;
00165   if (s == NULL) return 0;
00166   while (s[i] != '\0') i++;
00167   return i;
00168 }
00169 
00170 static GLuint _glewStrCLen (const GLubyte* s, GLubyte c)
00171 {
00172   GLuint i=0;
00173   if (s == NULL) return 0;
00174   while (s[i] != '\0' && s[i] != c) i++;
00175   return (s[i] == '\0' || s[i] == c) ? i : 0;
00176 }
00177 
00178 static GLboolean _glewStrSame (const GLubyte* a, const GLubyte* b, GLuint n)
00179 {
00180   GLuint i=0;
00181   if(a == NULL || b == NULL)
00182     return (a == NULL && b == NULL && n == 0) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
00183   while (i < n && a[i] != '\0' && b[i] != '\0' && a[i] == b[i]) i++;
00184   return i == n ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
00185 }
00186 
00187 static GLboolean _glewStrSame1 (GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
00188 {
00189   while (*na > 0 && (**a == ' ' || **a == '\n' || **a == '\r' || **a == '\t'))
00190   {
00191     (*a)++;
00192     (*na)--;
00193   }
00194   if(*na >= nb)
00195   {
00196     GLuint i=0;
00197     while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
00198         if(i == nb)
00199         {
00200                 *a = *a + nb;
00201                 *na = *na - nb;
00202                 return GL_TRUE;
00203         }
00204   }
00205   return GL_FALSE;
00206 }
00207 
00208 static GLboolean _glewStrSame2 (GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
00209 {
00210   if(*na >= nb)
00211   {
00212     GLuint i=0;
00213     while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
00214         if(i == nb)
00215         {
00216                 *a = *a + nb;
00217                 *na = *na - nb;
00218                 return GL_TRUE;
00219         }
00220   }
00221   return GL_FALSE;
00222 }
00223 
00224 static GLboolean _glewStrSame3 (GLubyte** a, GLuint* na, const GLubyte* b, GLuint nb)
00225 {
00226   if(*na >= nb)
00227   {
00228     GLuint i=0;
00229     while (i < nb && (*a)+i != NULL && b+i != NULL && (*a)[i] == b[i]) i++;
00230     if (i == nb && (*na == nb || (*a)[i] == ' ' || (*a)[i] == '\n' || (*a)[i] == '\r' || (*a)[i] == '\t'))
00231     {
00232       *a = *a + nb;
00233       *na = *na - nb;
00234       return GL_TRUE;
00235     }
00236   }
00237   return GL_FALSE;
00238 }

06795 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
06796 
06797 /* 
06798  * Search for name in the extensions string. Use of strstr()
06799  * is not sufficient because extension names can be prefixes of
06800  * other extension names. Could use strtok() but the constant
06801  * string returned by glGetString might be in read-only memory.
06802  */
06803 GLboolean glewGetExtension (const char* name)
06804 {    
06805   GLubyte* p;
06806   GLubyte* end;
06807   GLuint len = _glewStrLen((const GLubyte*)name);
06808   p = (GLubyte*)glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS);
06809   if (0 == p) return GL_FALSE;
06810   end = p + _glewStrLen(p);
06811   while (p < end)
06812   {
06813     GLuint n = _glewStrCLen(p, ' ');
06814     if (len == n && _glewStrSame((const GLubyte*)name, p, n)) return GL_TRUE;
06815     p += n+1;
06816   }
06817   return GL_FALSE;
06818 }
06819 
06820 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
06821 
06822 #ifndef GLEW_MX
06823 static
06824 #endif
06825 GLenum glewContextInit (GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
06826 {
06827   const GLubyte* s;
06828   GLuint dot;
06829   GLint major, minor;
06830   /* query opengl version */
06831   s = glGetString(GL_VERSION);
06832   dot = _glewStrCLen(s, '.');
06833   if (dot == 0)
06834     return GLEW_ERROR_NO_GL_VERSION;
06835   
06836   major = s[dot-1]-'0';
06837   minor = s[dot+1]-'0';
06838 
06839   if (minor < 0 || minor > 9)
06840     minor = 0;
06841   if (major<0 || major>9)
06842     return GLEW_ERROR_NO_GL_VERSION;
06843   
06844 
06845   if (major == 1 && minor == 0)
06846   {
06847     return GLEW_ERROR_GL_VERSION_10_ONLY;
06848   }
06849   else
06850   {
06851     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_2) = ( major > 3 )               || ( major == 3 && minor >= 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06852     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_1) = GLEW_VERSION_3_2 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 3 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06853     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_0) = GLEW_VERSION_3_1 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 3               ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06854     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_2_1) = GLEW_VERSION_3_0 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 2 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;    
06855     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_2_0) = GLEW_VERSION_2_1 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 2               ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06856     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_5) = GLEW_VERSION_2_0 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 5 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06857     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_4) = GLEW_VERSION_1_5 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 4 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06858     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_3) = GLEW_VERSION_1_4 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 3 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06859     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_2) = GLEW_VERSION_1_3 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 2 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06860     CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_1) = GLEW_VERSION_1_2 == GL_TRUE || ( major == 1 && minor >= 1 ) ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
06861   }
06862   /* initialize extensions */
06863 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_2
06864   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_1_2) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_2) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_1_2(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06865 #endif /* GL_VERSION_1_2 */
06866 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_3
06867   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_1_3) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_3) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_1_3(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06868 #endif /* GL_VERSION_1_3 */
06869 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_4
06870   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_1_4) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_4) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_1_4(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06871 #endif /* GL_VERSION_1_4 */
06872 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_5
06873   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_1_5) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_1_5) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_1_5(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06874 #endif /* GL_VERSION_1_5 */
06875 #ifdef GL_VERSION_2_0
06876   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_2_0) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_2_0) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_2_0(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06877 #endif /* GL_VERSION_2_0 */
06878 #ifdef GL_VERSION_2_1
06879   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_2_1) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_2_1) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_2_1(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06880 #endif /* GL_VERSION_2_1 */
06881 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_0
06882   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_3_0) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_0) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_3_0(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06883 #endif /* GL_VERSION_3_0 */
06884 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_1
06885   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_3_1) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_1) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_3_1(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
06886 #endif /* GL_VERSION_3_1 */
06887 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_2
06888   if (glewExperimental || GLEW_VERSION_3_2) CONST_CAST(GLEW_VERSION_3_2) = !_glewInit_GL_VERSION_3_2(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);

08797 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
08798 
08799 static PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGARBPROC _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB = NULL;
08800 static PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGEXTPROC _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT = NULL;
08801 
08802 GLboolean wglewGetExtension (const char* name)
08803 {    
08804   GLubyte* p;
08805   GLubyte* end;
08806   GLuint len = _glewStrLen((const GLubyte*)name);
08807   if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB == NULL)
08808     if (_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT == NULL)
08809       return GL_FALSE;
08810     else
08811       p = (GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT();
08812   else
08813     p = (GLubyte*)_wglewGetExtensionsStringARB(wglGetCurrentDC());
08814   if (0 == p) return GL_FALSE;
08815   end = p + _glewStrLen(p);
08816   while (p < end)
08817   {
08818     GLuint n = _glewStrCLen(p, ' ');
08819     if (len == n && _glewStrSame((const GLubyte*)name, p, n)) return GL_TRUE;
08820     p += n+1;
08821   }
08822   return GL_FALSE;
08823 }
08824 
08825 GLenum wglewContextInit (WGLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
08826 {
08827   GLboolean crippled;

08829   _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB = (PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGARBPROC)glewGetProcAddress((const GLubyte*)"wglGetExtensionsStringARB");
08830   _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT = (PFNWGLGETEXTENSIONSSTRINGEXTPROC)glewGetProcAddress((const GLubyte*)"wglGetExtensionsStringEXT");
08831   /* initialize extensions */
08832   crippled = _wglewGetExtensionsStringARB == NULL && _wglewGetExtensionsStringEXT == NULL;

09713 
09714 /* ------------------------------------------------------------------------ */
09715 
09716 GLboolean glxewGetExtension (const char* name)
09717 {    
09718   GLubyte* p;
09719   GLubyte* end;
09720   GLuint len;
09721 
09722   if (glXGetCurrentDisplay == NULL) return GL_FALSE;
09723   len = _glewStrLen((const GLubyte*)name);
09724   p = (GLubyte*)glXGetClientString(glXGetCurrentDisplay(), GLX_EXTENSIONS);
09725   if (0 == p) return GL_FALSE;
09726   end = p + _glewStrLen(p);
09727   while (p < end)
09728   {
09729     GLuint n = _glewStrCLen(p, ' ');
09730     if (len == n && _glewStrSame((const GLubyte*)name, p, n)) return GL_TRUE;
09731     p += n+1;
09732   }
09733   return GL_FALSE;
09734 }
09735 
09736 GLenum glxewContextInit (GLXEW_CONTEXT_ARG_DEF_LIST)
09737 {
09738   int major, minor;
09739   /* initialize core GLX 1.2 */
09740   if (_glewInit_GLX_VERSION_1_2(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT)) return GLEW_ERROR_GLX_VERSION_11_ONLY;
09741   /* initialize flags */
09742   CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_0) = GL_TRUE;
09743   CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_1) = GL_TRUE;
09744   CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_2) = GL_TRUE;
09745   CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_3) = GL_TRUE;
09746   CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_4) = GL_TRUE;
09747   /* query GLX version */
09748   glXQueryVersion(glXGetCurrentDisplay(), &major, &minor);
09749   if (major == 1 && minor <= 3)
09750   {
09751     switch (minor)
09752     {
09753       case 3:
09754       CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_4) = GL_FALSE;
09755       break;
09756       case 2:
09757       CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_4) = GL_FALSE;
09758       CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_3) = GL_FALSE;
09759       break;
09760       default:
09761       return GLEW_ERROR_GLX_VERSION_11_ONLY;
09762       break;
09763     }
09764   }
09765   /* initialize extensions */
09766 #ifdef GLX_VERSION_1_3
09767   if (glewExperimental || GLXEW_VERSION_1_3) CONST_CAST(GLXEW_VERSION_1_3) = !_glewInit_GLX_VERSION_1_3(GLEW_CONTEXT_ARG_VAR_INIT);
09768 #endif /* GLX_VERSION_1_3 */

09775 #endif /* GLX_ARB_create_context */

09949 
09950 const GLubyte* glewGetErrorString (GLenum error)
09951 {
09952   static const GLubyte* _glewErrorString[] =
09953   {
09954     (const GLubyte*)"No error",
09955     (const GLubyte*)"Missing GL version",
09956     (const GLubyte*)"GL 1.1 and up are not supported",
09957     (const GLubyte*)"GLX 1.2 and up are not supported",
09958     (const GLubyte*)"Unknown error"
09959   };
09960   const int max_error = sizeof(_glewErrorString)/sizeof(*_glewErrorString) - 1;
09961   return _glewErrorString[(int)error > max_error ? max_error : (int)error];
09962 }
09963 
09964 const GLubyte* glewGetString (GLenum name)
09965 {
09966   static const GLubyte* _glewString[] =
09967   {
09968     (const GLubyte*)NULL,
09969     (const GLubyte*)"1.5.3",
09970     (const GLubyte*)"1",
09971     (const GLubyte*)"5",
09972     (const GLubyte*)"3"
09973   };
09974   const int max_string = sizeof(_glewString)/sizeof(*_glewString) - 1;
09975   return _glewString[(int)name > max_string ? 0 : (int)name];
09976 }

09979 
09980 GLboolean glewExperimental = GL_FALSE;
09981 
09982 #if !defined(GLEW_MX)
09983 
09984 #if defined(_WIN32)
09985 extern GLenum wglewContextInit (void);
09986 #elif !defined(__APPLE__) || defined(GLEW_APPLE_GLX) /* _UNIX */
09987 extern GLenum glxewContextInit (void);
09988 #endif /* _WIN32 */
09989 
09990 GLenum glewInit ()
09991 {
09992   GLenum r;
09993   if ( (r = glewContextInit()) ) return r;
09994 #if defined(_WIN32)
09995   return wglewContextInit();
09996 #elif !defined(__APPLE__) || defined(GLEW_APPLE_GLX) /* _UNIX */
09997   return glxewContextInit();
09998 #else
09999   return r;
10000 #endif /* _WIN32 */
10001 }
10002 
10003 #endif /* !GLEW_MX */
10004 #ifdef GLEW_MX
10005 GLboolean glewContextIsSupported (GLEWContext* ctx, const char* name)
10006 #else
10007 GLboolean glewIsSupported (const char* name)
10008 #endif
10009 {
10010   GLubyte* pos = (GLubyte*)name;
10011   GLuint len = _glewStrLen(pos);
10012   GLboolean ret = GL_TRUE;
10013   while (ret && len > 0)
10014   {
10015     if (_glewStrSame1(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"GL_", 3))
10016     {
10017       if (_glewStrSame2(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"VERSION_", 8))
10018       {
10019 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_2
10020         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_2", 3))
10021         {
10022           ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_2;
10023           continue;
10024         }
10025 #endif
10026 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_3
10027         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_3", 3))
10028         {
10029           ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_3;
10030           continue;
10031         }
10032 #endif
10033 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_4
10034         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_4", 3))
10035         {
10036           ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_4;
10037           continue;
10038         }
10039 #endif
10040 #ifdef GL_VERSION_1_5
10041         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"1_5", 3))
10042         {
10043           ret = GLEW_VERSION_1_5;
10044           continue;
10045         }
10046 #endif
10047 #ifdef GL_VERSION_2_0
10048         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"2_0", 3))
10049         {
10050           ret = GLEW_VERSION_2_0;
10051           continue;
10052         }
10053 #endif
10054 #ifdef GL_VERSION_2_1
10055         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"2_1", 3))
10056         {
10057           ret = GLEW_VERSION_2_1;
10058           continue;
10059         }
10060 #endif
10061 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_0
10062         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"3_0", 3))
10063         {
10064           ret = GLEW_VERSION_3_0;
10065           continue;
10066         }
10067 #endif
10068 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_1
10069         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"3_1", 3))
10070         {
10071           ret = GLEW_VERSION_3_1;
10072           continue;
10073         }
10074 #endif
10075 #ifdef GL_VERSION_3_2
10076         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"3_2", 3))
10077         {
10078           ret = GLEW_VERSION_3_2;
10079           continue;
10080         }
10081 #endif
10082       }
10083       if (_glewStrSame2(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"3DFX_", 5))
10084       {
10085 #ifdef GL_3DFX_multisample
10086         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"multisample", 11))
10087         {
10088           ret = GLEW_3DFX_multisample;
10089           continue;
10090         }
10091 #endif
10092 #ifdef GL_3DFX_tbuffer
10093         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"tbuffer", 7))
10094         {
10095           ret = GLEW_3DFX_tbuffer;
10096           continue;
10097         }
10098 #endif
10099 #ifdef GL_3DFX_texture_compression_FXT1
10100         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"texture_compression_FXT1", 24))
10101         {
10102           ret = GLEW_3DFX_texture_compression_FXT1;
10103           continue;
10104         }
10105 #endif
10106       }
10107       if (_glewStrSame2(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"AMD_", 4))
10108       {
10109 #ifdef GL_AMD_draw_buffers_blend
10110         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"draw_buffers_blend", 18))
10111         {
10112           ret = GLEW_AMD_draw_buffers_blend;
10113           continue;
10114         }
10115 #endif
10116 #ifdef GL_AMD_performance_monitor
10117         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"performance_monitor", 19))
10118         {
10119           ret = GLEW_AMD_performance_monitor;
10120           continue;
10121         }
10122 #endif
10123 #ifdef GL_AMD_seamless_cubemap_per_texture
10124         if (_glewStrSame3(&pos, &len, (const GLubyte*)"seamless_cubemap_per_texture", 28))
10125         {
10126           ret = GLEW_AMD_seamless_cubemap_per_texture;
10127           continue;
10128         }
